<HEAD>
<TITLE> Business Leadership Council</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=5><B>Business Leadership Council</B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=2><B><I>THE FREE ENTERPRISE BUSINESS ASSOCIATION</I></B></FONT>
<BR></CENTER>
<HR>
<P>
The Business Leadership Council (BLC) is dedicated to free market principles, economic opportunity, private property rights, and individual liberty.  It represents businesses that are entrepreneurial, growth-oriented, and supporters of free enterprise, as



 opposed to those which want to protect the status quo or are seeking special government privileges.  Its members are business leaders who are willing to take bold, principled positions in support of issues such as limiting the size of government and expa



nding global economic freedom.
<P>
The Business Leadership Council has formed the Tax Alternatives Working Group (TAWG) in order to analyze each of the major competing tax alternative proposals currently under consideration and to provide input from a business point of view to the leading 



proponents of these reforms, to others in the Congress and to the general public.  The objective is to make a positive contribution to improving all of the alternative tax proposals; and to ensure that the various tax plans will be better able to meet the



 goals of promoting economic growth in a way that takes into account the practical concerns of the business community.
<P>
<CENTER><B>Business Leadership Council<BR>
Suite 201<BR>
1020 16th Street, N.W.<BR>
Washington, D.C.  20036<BR>
<P>
Phone:  202/659-5252<BR>
Fax:  202/659-3215<BR></B></CENTER>
