<title>October 7, 1996 Press Release</title>

<body>

<font size=-1>

FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE<br>
October 7, 1996<br>
CONTACT: Kristi S. Hamrick -- (202) 393-2100 & Michael Johnston (757) 
872-8878. For Radio: Kristin Hansen.
</font>

<p>

<center><u><h4>MEDIA ADVISORY:</h4></u>

<p>

<h2>2ND ANNUAL NATIONAL COMING <i>OUT OF</i><br>
HOMOSEXUALITY DAY ... THURSDAY, OCT. 10<br>
<u><i>AND, AT THE SAME EVENT,</i></u><br>
PRO-FAMILY AND GRASSROOTS LEADERS UNITE<br>
TO UNVEIL NEW, NATIONAL ORGANIZATION<br>
PFOX<br>
Parents and Friends of Ex-Gays</h2></center>

<p>

<b>WASHINGTON, D.C. --</b> Timed in conjunction with National
Coming Out Day, which is organized to affirm the homosexual lifestyle,
a Thursday news conference will focus on the other options and
organizations that are available to help people struggling with
homosexuality.

<p>

National organizer Michael Johnston, a former homosexual who is
HIV-positive, has joined with more than 100  local and national
organizations to coordinate the second annual &quot;National Coming
Out of Homosexuality Day.&quot; Coming Out of Homosexuality Day
is a project organized to counter the events of the Human Rights
Campaign, which works to further the agenda of homosexual activists.

<p>

<b>The news event, co-sponsored by Family Research Council,  will
be at: 9:30 a.m. Thursday, Oct. 10, in the Zenger Room of the
National Press Club.</b>

<p>

The news event will include the exciting unveiling of a parents
and friends organization -- PFOX, Parents and Friends of Ex-Gays,
an outgrowth of  D.C.- based Transformation Ministries. PFOX was
organized to provide family viewpoints ignored by PFLAG, the pro-homosexual
parents organization.

<p>

<b>On Friday, Oct. 11, National Coming Out of Homosexuality Day
organizers will also host a time of testimonials, sharing and
outreach from 10 a.m. to 11 a.m. The media are welcome to talk
with former homosexuals at this event geared for reaching out
to practicing homosexuals about their other options. The location:
TBA, but it will be organized around the AIDS quilt activities.</b>

<p>

<center><h4>FOR MORE INFORMATION OR INTERVIEWS,<br>
CONTACT THE FRC MEDIA OFFICE AT (202) 393-2100.</h4></center>

<p>

