<html>

<title>Daily Commentary - December 17, 1996</title>

<body>

<center><h1>Daily Commentary<br>
December 17, 1996</h1></center>

<p><hr width=75% size=3><p>

I'm Gary Bauer for Washington Watch.

<p>

Bill Clinton has gone on the warpath again, this time taking
aim at talk radio.  Appearing on a popular talk show, Clinton
denounced talk radio as &quot;overwhelmingly right wing,&quot;
and said it doesn't serve the country well.  Well, I'll concede
one point.  Talk radio can sometimes be crass and crude.  Some
hosts believe you have to offend to get an audience.

<p>

But someone needs to remind the president of something. 
It takes gall to denounce one of the few unstructured forums in
this country for political speech.  Like most politicians, Clinton
ran a tightly controlled, carefully scripted campaign this year.
Talk radio, on the other hand, at least reflects some genuine
give-and-take among average Americans.  Own a phone and you can
be part of the conversation.

<p>

America is a land of freedom, and millions of men and women
have shed blood to keep it that way.  The last thing today's citizens
want or need is a lecture from the just re-elected president of
the United States that their views shouldn't be aired.  After
all, isn't having our say the American way?

<p>

For the Family Research Council, this is Gary Bauer with
today's Washington Watch.  For more information about us, call
1-800-225-4008.  That number again:  1-800-225-4008.

<p>

